summary:
Chaos on Capitol Hill. A series of clips. At the entrance of the Tunnel. At the right of the tunnel entrance. People chanting "No Trump. No Peace." IAmBlakeMarnell seen in the crowd.  
At 7:34 BlackGlove805 gives a speech to the crowd on a bullhorn. "Patriots we've made it this far. Be quiet. We've spoken to 'em. Their holding the line. They say that, they will not mace us, tase us, or beat us. We're holding the line. We're not moving until we get our way (applause) This is a peaceful protest now. They always ask it. Remember, Remember. This is our capitol. This is our house. These our our steps. If we have to sit here all night. Do not [...] we are trying to work with them. Do you understand Patriots? Look we are doing all we can. I'm not on their side."   
10:17 (cut) Riot chants "Fight for Trump." People pushing at the officers, pinning BlackGlove805 at the officers  
11:35 ScaryCherry3P surfing the crowd to fight the officers.  
At 11:49, someone in black tactical gear and a flag mask hits officers with crutches. Mace sends people tumbling down the steps. #Scallops gives the finger at 12:12 and hits officers with crutches at 12:31. At 12:51, people are passing tables and furniture out of the shattered window in the Capitol.  
At 13:44 someone plays Trumps video over a Megaphone

summary:
Video by justus_eapen. In the crowd on the Lower Western Terrace stairs leading up to the Arched Tunnel Entrance. Police riot shields are seen being passed overhead.   
At 2:45 a male subject is being led away while struggling with the effects of pepper spray.   
At 2:47 he turns his back to camera and exposes his helmet name tag. Patch reads K. Jackson N.L.V.   
At 5:57 a caption appears on the video: "They just dragged a cop out of the Capitol ... For a minute I thought they were gonna throw him over the side."  In foreground, a blond man in tan jacket waves at people to cut it out. Caption continues:  "He was crying. Definitely thought he was going to die."    
6:36 - Video moves closer. we see officer's helmet is MPDC.   
At 6:40 profile of officer's face - it is Michael Fanone. Someone grabs his hand, as if to pull him up the steps, but the mob is difficult to move. He eventually is maneuvered back up. Meanwhile, other officers on the right of the arch are being punched with fists and struck with riot shields.   
At 8:12 #BlackGlove805 yells into megaphone that "We are not moving until we get our way!" Yup. That's how democracy works.

41:05 An orange pilon is seen thrown into the tunnel opening. (4:52 pm)  
41:23 Interview with a man who is looking for his son, Caden. Man says he is from Washington State. Cameraman pans the crowd, the West Plaza stage seems to be less full at this point. Brief dip in footage as the camera battery is changed.  
44:22 Stream footage resumes.  
44:51 PinStripeBoilerSuit pushing a roll of canvas at the cops in the tunnel entrance. Steps back and throws an object at police. Grabs a big camo fabric object (a tarp maybe) and holds it up to block police view. Strikes at officers with a wooden object.  
45:30 A speaker is thrown at the officers. "USA, USA" chants from the crowd. People at the entrance are again hitting at officers with a SeditionBat and a broken piece of furniture. (4:57 pm)  
Cameraman pans the crowd again. Officers have cleared the Upper West Terrace. Crowd is thinning on the West Plaza. at 47:25 back to the view of the tunnel, strobe type of light seen inside.  
48:07 Another orange pilon is thrown at officers.  
49:39 PinStripeBoilerSuit throws an orange pylon at officers. Another round of fighting officers follows.  
50:05 Brick Suit joins commentary and talks about how he believes the vandalism is largely from Antifa.  
50:18 People in the room at the Left of Tunnel window have brought an interior door out. BullhornLady is nearby.  
51:21 Green smoke comes out of the tunnel. It quickly becomes very thick. PinStripeBoilerSuit again striking at officers.   
52:07 Flashbang at the tunnel entrance (5:03 pm)  
52:28 An officer emerges at the tunnel with a weapon and is aiming it toward the crowd. (5:04 pm) Crowd reciprocates with some smoke bombs thrown in the direction of the police.  
53:03 Two flashes seen at the tunnel entrance, large amounts of tear gas fill the Lower West Terrace. The crowd begins to disperse.  
53:15 A series of additional tear gas flashes are seen. The crowd is quickly leaving the area.  
53:44 The smoke clears enough to see that the Lower West Terrace is largely clear, and people have been pushed in the direction of the stairs. Police are emerging from the tunnel and taking formation on the steps.   
Cameraman in the crush of people as they leave the Terrace.

They lifted up my gas mask and sprayed me in the face beating us in the head with batons. So we knew we couldn't get through the doors. So we broke the window got into the room. At that point it was all over my hair my face, I couldn't breath, I couldn't see. So I, we had to come up with a plan. What ended up happening was a man's father called him from the outside and said the media is calling it anarchists. And what that means is they now have access to use deadly force against us. We lost lives in there. Two confirmed lives have been lost. Patriots we took the capitol and we're not stopping. I will be back tonight. I couldn't see I couldn't breath but we're not backing down we got the outside we got the outside we will take it back... you don't want to talk this is how we do it. 1776 is back. 2021 United we stand. with biden we fall."
